Key Match Events: The Clippers overcame fatigue to secure a 105-103 win over the Toronto Raptors.
Norman Powell scored 24 points despite being tired.
James Harden contributed 24 points, 12 rebounds, and 7 assists.
Ivica Zubac added 14 points and 12 rebounds.
Terance Mann played stellar defense, including a crucial block on Immanuel Quickley.
Immanuel Quickley tied the score 102-102 with a three-pointer with 39 seconds left.
Norman Powell made a free throw to retake the lead for the Clippers.
James Harden made one of two free throws in the final seconds.
Jakob Poeltl intentionally missed a free throw in an attempt to score on a putback but missed.
Ivica Zubac secured the rebound with 2.5 seconds left, sealing the win.
Post-Match Reflections: Tyronn Lue acknowledged the fatigue of his players and emphasized the importance of the win.
James Harden commented on the tough schedule and the need to find ways to win games.
Norman Powell reflected on his fatigue and the need to stay in the moment and find a way to win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kawhi Leonard has not played this season due to inflammation in his right knee and will not travel with the team on their upcoming trip.
Mo Bamba, who hasn't played this season due to a knee injury, is progressing and participating in practice sessions.
